# ipam_ip_range (Data Source)

Reads an existing IP range by name or ID. Use this when one Terraform stack allocates a range and another stack only needs to read its CIDR — without creating a duplicate resource.

When the range is managed in the same stack, use `id` to reference the resource directly. This avoids stale lookups when multiple ranges share the same name in the database.

## Example Usage

### Cross-stack lookup by name

```hcl
data "ipam_ip_range" "gke_nodes" {
  name = "prod-gke-nodes"
}

resource "google_container_cluster" "primary" {
  # ...
  cluster_ipv4_cidr = data.ipam_ip_range.gke_nodes.cidr
}
```

### Same-stack lookup by ID

```hcl
resource "ipam_ip_range" "gke_nodes" {
  name       = "prod-gke-nodes"
  range_size = 22
  domain     = ipam_routing_domain.prod.id
  parent     = ipam_ip_range.root.cidr
}

data "ipam_ip_range" "gke_nodes" {
  id = ipam_ip_range.gke_nodes.id
}
```

